## Feature Documentation Structure

The feature documentation follows this structure:

```
/product/features/<feature_name>/
  ├── overview.md           # High-level overview of the feature
  └── user_stories/         # Directory containing user stories
      ├── story1.md         # Individual user story files
      ├── story2.md
      └── ...
```

### Overview Document Format (`overview.md`)

```markdown
# Feature Name: [Feature Name]

## High level overview
[One paragraph overview of the feature, its need, and implementation]

## High level tasking
- [Task 1]
- [Task 2]
- [Task 3]
- ...

## Analysis of complexity
[Left blank for Role #2 LLM Agent]
```

### User Story Format

```markdown
# User Story: [Story Title]

## Description
As a [user type], I want [goal], so that [benefit].

## Acceptance Criteria
- [Criterion 1]
- [Criterion 2]
- [Criterion 3]
- ...

## Notes
[Additional context, edge cases, or considerations]
```

## PRD Breakdown Process

The PRD breakdown process follows these steps to transform high-level requirements into AI-implementable units:

### 1. Requirement Identification
- Extract core requirements from product/ROADMAP.md
- Identify user stories and use cases
- Document business logic requirements
- Define acceptance criteria for each requirement

### 2. Feature Overview Creation
- Create `overview.md` with a clear, concise explanation of the feature
- List high-level tasks required for implementation
- Ensure alignment with product vision and user needs

### 3. User Story Development
- Create individual user stories in the `user_stories/` directory
- Focus on user value and benefits, not technical implementation
- Define clear, testable acceptance criteria
- Provide additional context and notes as needed

### 4. Documentation Review
- Ensure all user stories collectively cover the entire feature scope
- Verify that acceptance criteria are specific and measurable
- Check alignment with product vision and overall roadmap
- Confirm clarity and completeness for technical implementation

### 5. Handoff for Next Role
- Prepare feature documentation for review by Role #2
- Support the next role in understanding requirements
- Clarify requirements as needed

